Answer.feedback: As an experienced Turker, I know enough to scroll to the bottom of the page that has the completion code on it, and look for a "Next" or ">>" or a "Continue" button. (And sure enough, there indeed was a continue button and a single page after that!..though to be fair, the final page also had a completion code on it, which I'm gonna give you praise for, because that's a really good idea to do.) However, you might want to factor-in that some Turkers might not be aware that they need to look for a continue button on the very page that shows them the completion code, and thus might accidently close the tab or window at that point, assuming they were done. Of course, if you use "over 5000 completed HITs" or something similar (please do NOT use "Masters" qual, however, as Amazon from all appearances doesn't give that out anymore) as a qualification, though, I doubt it would be any sort of issue...since then your survey takers would all be experienced and know the ins and outs and quirks of the website. Thanks!
